## FAQ section

vpn-landing-faq-heading = FAQs
vpn-landing-faq-devices-question-heading = What devices is the { -brand-name-mozilla-vpn } compatible with?
vpn-landing-faq-devices-question-desc = The { -brand-name-mozilla-vpn } clients are compatible with { -brand-name-windows } 10 (64-bit only), { -brand-name-mac-short } (10.15 and up), { -brand-name-android } (version 6 and up), { -brand-name-ios } (13.0 and up), and { -brand-name-linux } ({ -brand-name-ubuntu }-only).
vpn-landing-faq-info-question-heading = What information does the { -brand-name-mozilla-vpn } keep?

# Variables:
#   $privacy (url) - link to https://www.mozilla.org/privacy/principles/
vpn-landing-faq-info-question-desc = We don’t log, track, or share any of your network activity. We adhere strictly to { -brand-name-mozilla }’s <a href="{ $privacy }">Data Privacy Principles</a>, and we only collect the most minimal data required to keep the VPN healthy and operational.

vpn-landing-faq-protected-question-heading = How is my privacy protected?
vpn-landing-faq-protected-question-desc = { -brand-name-wireguard }® protocol encrypts your network traffic protecting all your private information. Compared to existing VPN protocols, WireGuard’s lightweight code is easier for security analysts to review and audit - making it a more secure option for the VPN. In addition, your online activities can stay anonymous because we never log, track or share your network data.
vpn-landing-faq-refund-question-heading = What is the { -brand-name-mozilla-vpn }’s refund policy?
vpn-landing-faq-refund-question-desc = You can get your money back within 30-days of purchasing the subscription. Contact us and submit the refund request by tapping the Get Help button in Settings on your app.
vpn-landing-faq-link = See more FAQs

